WEBVTT

1
00:00:40.082 --> 00:00:42.376 line:80%
2005

2
00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:51.010 line:80%
-Yu Ji-hyuk!
-Yu Ji-hyuk!

3
00:00:51.093 --> 00:00:52.511 line:80%
-Congrats!
-Congrats!

4
00:00:52.595 --> 00:00:54.764 line:80%
-On your 100-day
-On your 100-day...

5
00:00:54.847 --> 00:00:56.182 line:80%
vacation!

6
00:01:06.484 --> 00:01:10.112 line:80%
Did you sign up for manual labor
instead of the military?

7
00:01:10.196 --> 00:01:11.530 line:80%
What's with your face?

8
00:01:11.822 --> 00:01:13.616 line:80%
I thought you renounced the world.

9
00:01:14.241 --> 00:01:16.076 line:80%
Haven't you heard of sunscreen?

10
00:01:16.160 --> 00:01:18.871 line:80%
Of course,
it was around before you joined too.

11
00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:21.332 line:80%
What shall we eat now?

12
00:01:21.415 --> 00:01:23.417 line:80%
We spent a lot of money.

13
00:01:23.501 --> 00:01:26.128 line:80%
Let's buy soju and go back to school.

14
00:01:26.212 --> 00:01:27.755 line:80%
It's a good night!

15
00:01:33.886 --> 00:01:35.095 line:80%
Thank you.

16
00:01:40.392 --> 00:01:41.477 line:80%
What's that?

17
00:01:45.564 --> 00:01:46.690 line:80%
Go.

18
00:01:46.774 --> 00:01:49.652 line:80%
She shouldn't have drank so much.
That scared me.

19
00:01:49.777 --> 00:01:51.320 line:80%
Sorry about that!

20
00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:53.864 line:80%
I'm sorry.

21
00:02:00.496 --> 00:02:02.414 line:80%
Is she alone? Shall we take her?

22
00:02:02.498 --> 00:02:04.458 line:80%
She's begging for it.

23
00:02:04.542 --> 00:02:06.377 line:80%
Ignoring her wouldn't be polite.

24
00:02:06.460 --> 00:02:08.921 line:80%
Absolutely. That wouldn't be chivalrous.

25
00:02:09.380 --> 00:02:10.381 line:80%
Attack!

26
00:02:13.843 --> 00:02:15.052 line:80%
-Who's that?
-Who's that?

27
00:02:17.721 --> 00:02:18.973 line:80%
Are you okay?

28
00:02:19.056 --> 00:02:20.266 line:80%
A pole...

29
00:02:20.349 --> 00:02:21.559 line:80%
Sorry.

30
00:02:24.061 --> 00:02:25.187 line:80%
Are you okay?

31
00:02:26.856 --> 00:02:28.941 line:80%
Are you alone? Are you with anyone?

32
00:02:29.483 --> 00:02:30.901 line:80%
I'm alone.

33
00:02:31.986 --> 00:02:34.989 line:80%
I'm completely alone. Seriously alone.

34
00:02:38.617 --> 00:02:41.203 line:80%
My dad passed away on March 2nd.

35
00:02:41.287 --> 00:02:42.413 line:80%
So,

36
00:02:43.122 --> 00:02:44.290 line:80%
I'm alone.

37
00:02:46.083 --> 00:02:48.961 line:80%
Also, my boyfriend and I broke up.

38
00:02:49.044 --> 00:02:50.880 line:80%
So I'm seriously alone.

39
00:02:53.382 --> 00:02:55.050 line:80%
What about a friend?

40
00:02:55.134 --> 00:02:56.886 line:80%
I'm sure you have a friend.

41
00:03:00.681 --> 00:03:01.807 line:80%
A friend...

42
00:03:23.996 --> 00:03:29.209 line:80%
People don't like me,
so I have no friends.

43
00:03:35.841 --> 00:03:36.842 line:80%
I smell alcohol.

44
00:03:50.064 --> 00:03:51.231 line:80%
What's wrong?

45
00:03:55.736 --> 00:03:57.196 line:80%
It smells good.

46
00:03:57.947 --> 00:03:58.948 line:80%
Excuse me?

47
00:04:29.937 --> 00:04:31.730 line:80%
EPISODE 5

48
00:04:45.160 --> 00:04:46.662 line:80%
What do you want to know?

49
00:04:47.746 --> 00:04:52.501 line:80%
I want to know if this is beer or soju.

50
00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:55.629 line:80%
I have terrible vision.

51
00:04:56.505 --> 00:04:59.174 line:80%
You can tell this is beer
with your eyes shut!

52
00:04:59.258 --> 00:05:00.634 line:80%
If you can't tell that,

53
00:05:00.718 --> 00:05:03.220 line:80%
then you
probably shouldn't drink any more.

54
00:05:07.599 --> 00:05:09.560 line:80%
But I bought this beer.

55
00:05:10.853 --> 00:05:12.354 line:80%
Goodness.

56
00:05:13.147 --> 00:05:14.398 line:80%
Thank you.

57
00:05:14.982 --> 00:05:16.608 line:80%
Doesn't your forehead hurt?

58
00:05:16.692 --> 00:05:17.818 line:80%
It doesn't hurt.

59
00:05:20.821 --> 00:05:23.949 line:80%
But I really am allowed to drink tonight.

60
00:05:24.616 --> 00:05:26.452 line:80%
Then drink at your place.

61
00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:32.166 line:80%
You want me to drink alone?
I'm always alone.

62
00:05:38.297 --> 00:05:41.884 line:80%
My dad passed away three months ago.

63
00:05:41.967 --> 00:05:43.052 line:80%
March 2nd.

64
00:05:43.135 --> 00:05:45.971 line:80%
I know, and you broke up
with your boyfriend too.

65
00:05:47.181 --> 00:05:50.642 line:80%
Do you have other family?
Where's your mom? Do you have siblings?

66
00:05:52.352 --> 00:05:54.271 line:80%
I don't have siblings.

67
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:59.068 line:80%
My mom left home 3,193 days ago.

68
00:05:59.985 --> 00:06:02.112 line:80%
I was in middle school.

69
00:06:02.196 --> 00:06:05.282 line:80%
Also, friends--

70
00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:07.785 line:80%
No one likes you, so you have no friends.

71
00:06:08.702 --> 00:06:10.162 line:80%
How did you know?

72
00:06:15.584 --> 00:06:17.086 line:80%
Are you a fortune teller?

73
00:06:24.009 --> 00:06:25.385 line:80%
Here's your beer.

74
00:06:25.469 --> 00:06:26.970 line:80%
Thank you.

75
00:06:36.313 --> 00:06:38.148 line:80%
Beer's the best!

76
00:06:52.454 --> 00:06:54.498 line:80%
Actually, I do have one friend.

77
00:06:57.251 --> 00:06:59.503 line:80%
But I can't reach her

78
00:07:00.838 --> 00:07:04.049 line:80%
when I need her
and am having a really hard time.

79
00:07:05.217 --> 00:07:06.510 line:80%
Maybe she's busy.

80
00:07:07.469 --> 00:07:10.514 line:80%
I know. We have such bad timing.

81
00:07:10.973 --> 00:07:15.060 line:80%
I'm sure she wants to be with me too.

82
00:07:15.144 --> 00:07:16.311 line:80%
I'm sure she's sad.

83
00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:26.029 line:80%
But...

84
00:07:27.614 --> 00:07:29.366 line:80%
I think if I was with Su-min

85
00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:33.954 line:80%
on a day like this,

86
00:07:35.330 --> 00:07:36.957 line:80%
I'd feel like a loser.

87
00:07:48.051 --> 00:07:49.803 line:80%
My boyfriend

88
00:07:50.721 --> 00:07:52.389 line:80%
suddenly started being busy,

89
00:07:53.515 --> 00:07:55.726 line:80%
and he said he was always tired.

90
00:07:57.519 --> 00:08:01.607 line:80%
When my dad passed,

91
00:08:01.690 --> 00:08:03.317 line:80%
he didn't even come.

92
00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:07.279 line:80%
That's when it hit me.

93
00:08:09.156 --> 00:08:11.408 line:80%
Still, I pretended not to know.

94
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:13.785 line:80%
For three months at that!

95
00:08:15.537 --> 00:08:16.705 line:80%
Because...

96
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:21.585 line:80%
being alone

97
00:08:23.754 --> 00:08:25.214 line:80%
would only be sadder.

98
00:08:38.852 --> 00:08:39.853 line:80%
So my boyfriend...

99
00:08:43.232 --> 00:08:47.277 line:80%
I noticed that he's been smiling
at Su-min a lot.

100
00:08:48.946 --> 00:08:50.781 line:80%
But that's natural.

101
00:08:51.949 --> 00:08:56.286 line:80%
Su-min's nice, pretty, and cute.

102
00:08:57.537 --> 00:09:02.334 line:80%
Also, she's my only friend.

103
00:09:08.382 --> 00:09:10.092 line:80%
Do you know that feeling?

104
00:09:10.968 --> 00:09:15.347 line:80%
I'm sure Su-min's nice,

105
00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:19.434 line:80%
pretty, and cute.

106
00:09:22.437 --> 00:09:24.398 line:80%
But when I stand beside her,

107
00:09:27.442 --> 00:09:28.652 line:80%
I feel so shabby.

108
00:09:31.571 --> 00:09:34.491 line:80%
Like a big fat loser.

109
00:09:36.285 --> 00:09:39.413 line:80%
If that's how she makes you feel,
don't be her friend.

110
00:09:40.122 --> 00:09:43.208 line:80%
Who cares if she's good or bad?
You're uncomfortable.

111
00:09:43.292 --> 00:09:44.668 line:80%
Isn't she bad for you?

112
00:09:52.175 --> 00:09:54.928 line:80%
Do you know what it means
to not have a family?

113
00:10:00.017 --> 00:10:01.435 line:80%
Have you been on a boat?

114
00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:06.815 line:80%
After my dad died,

115
00:10:07.482 --> 00:10:10.485 line:80%
it feels like I'm on a boat every day.

116
00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:16.825 line:80%
My feet are firmly planted,
but the boat keeps rocking.

117
00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:19.286 line:80%
I feel anxious.

118
00:10:23.749 --> 00:10:25.792 line:80%
I want stability.

119
00:10:29.546 --> 00:10:31.798 line:80%
I want to step on solid land.

120
00:10:35.177 --> 00:10:38.930 line:80%
Su-min's the only one who will be my land.

121
00:10:42.351 --> 00:10:44.269 line:80%
I only have her.

122
00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:52.319 line:80%
But this is because I'm a loser. The end.

123
00:10:55.405 --> 00:10:57.407 line:80%
I guess that makes me a loser too.

124
00:10:59.242 --> 00:11:01.912 line:80%
My mom passed away 15 years ago.

125
00:11:01.995 --> 00:11:03.580 line:80%
Exactly 5,328 days ago.

126
00:11:05.374 --> 00:11:08.377 line:80%
After some time, I got a stepmother
and a younger sibling.

127
00:11:10.587 --> 00:11:13.006 line:80%
They're good people, but I feel strange.

128
00:11:13.799 --> 00:11:14.925 line:80%
I hate it.

129
00:11:16.676 --> 00:11:18.345 line:80%
Wow, you really are a loser.

130
00:11:21.390 --> 00:11:23.433 line:80%
I should get a grip.

131
00:11:23.517 --> 00:11:26.520 line:80%
The real loser was right here.

132
00:11:27.687 --> 00:11:31.400 line:80%
I mean, what happened to your mom is sad,

133
00:11:31.483 --> 00:11:35.404 line:80%
but the fact that your dad
could start over is a good thing, right?

134
00:11:39.241 --> 00:11:41.034 line:80%
My dad should've done that.

135
00:11:42.035 --> 00:11:43.120 line:80%
If he had...

136
00:11:46.456 --> 00:11:48.417 line:80%
he wouldn't have died.

137
00:11:54.923 --> 00:11:57.676 line:80%
My dad was able to start over,
but he died too.

138
00:11:58.260 --> 00:11:59.511 line:80%
Don't think that way.

139
00:12:06.435 --> 00:12:07.436 line:80%
Cheers.

140
00:12:10.021 --> 00:12:11.356 line:80%
You're so warm.

141
00:12:29.207 --> 00:12:32.169 line:80%
Let's just say we're both not losers.

142
00:12:33.670 --> 00:12:39.009 line:80%
Still, you're right about one thing.
My dad was happy before he died.

143
00:12:42.512 --> 00:12:46.725 line:80%
Your dad left you with a new family.

144
00:12:46.808 --> 00:12:47.851 line:80%
Congratulations!

145
00:12:51.313 --> 00:12:53.815 line:80%
Congrats on having a solid friend.

146
00:12:56.151 --> 00:12:57.194 line:80%
No.

147
00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:03.909 line:80%
You're able to have
a good and solid friend.

148
00:13:06.953 --> 00:13:08.038 line:80%
Congratulations.

149
00:14:58.315 --> 00:15:01.776 line:80%
STIR-FRIED ATHLETES
SPORTS CLUB

150
00:15:37.687 --> 00:15:40.148 line:80%
Yu Ji-hyuk wins!

151
00:15:42.275 --> 00:15:43.276 line:80%
Ji-hyuk.

152
00:15:46.863 --> 00:15:49.491 line:80%
Jo Dong-suk,
a reserve for the national team,

153
00:15:49.574 --> 00:15:52.452 line:80%
has been beaten by
an ordinary economics student.

154
00:15:56.873 --> 00:15:58.041 line:80%
Why?

155
00:15:58.583 --> 00:16:01.628 line:80%
Why are you going this far?

156
00:16:01.711 --> 00:16:03.546 line:80%
You're a civilian!

157
00:16:03.630 --> 00:16:05.423 line:80%
You're not a pro athlete!

158
00:16:05.507 --> 00:16:07.801 line:80%
You're a soldier. Let's take ten.

159
00:16:07.884 --> 00:16:09.052 line:80%
What?

160
00:16:11.763 --> 00:16:13.014 line:80%
You want to go again?

161
00:16:13.431 --> 00:16:14.724 line:80%
I think he does.

162
00:16:14.808 --> 00:16:17.185 line:80%
Why did he go into economics then?

163
00:16:23.650 --> 00:16:25.360 line:80%
I woke up,

164
00:16:25.443 --> 00:16:29.406 line:80%
and I was snoring beside
an unpleasant-looking old man!

165
00:16:35.078 --> 00:16:36.204 line:80%
I was so surprised.

166
00:16:37.706 --> 00:16:40.458 line:80%
I hope he doesn't go to our school.

167
00:16:41.251 --> 00:16:43.086 line:80%
That would be so embarrassing.

168
00:16:43.169 --> 00:16:44.504 line:80%
I hate that.

169
00:16:45.463 --> 00:16:47.799 line:80%
But he was strange too.

170
00:16:47.882 --> 00:16:49.843 line:80%
Why do that with a drunk girl?

171
00:16:51.094 --> 00:16:52.637 line:80%
-I mean...
-True.

172
00:16:53.221 --> 00:16:54.806 line:80%
I need to get a grip.

173
00:16:55.473 --> 00:16:57.434 line:80%
I'm already 23.

174
00:16:57.517 --> 00:16:58.768 line:80%
When will I grow up?

175
00:17:07.402 --> 00:17:08.903 line:80%
She was an upperclassman?

176
00:17:13.283 --> 00:17:16.453 line:80%
Since we're at it, can you beat Sin-u too?
For real!

177
00:17:16.536 --> 00:17:19.289 line:80%
-I quit judo.
-Please, I'm begging you.

178
00:17:19.372 --> 00:17:20.540 line:80%
Well?

179
00:17:23.334 --> 00:17:24.377 line:80%
Why?

180
00:17:24.461 --> 00:17:25.754 line:80%
Is something wrong?

181
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:38.892 line:80%
I was snoring beside
an unpleasant-looking old man!

182
00:17:41.144 --> 00:17:42.145 line:80%
Hey.

183
00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:45.356 line:80%
Am I an unpleasant-looking old man?

184
00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:47.400 line:80%
Which part do you mean?

185
00:17:47.484 --> 00:17:49.819 line:80%
The unpleasant-looking or old man part?

186
00:17:50.236 --> 00:17:52.614 line:80%
Do you want me to recommend a sunscreen?

187
00:17:55.116 --> 00:17:56.242 line:80%
What about now?

188
00:17:56.326 --> 00:17:58.495 line:80%
-That's good.
-Good.

189
00:17:58.578 --> 00:17:59.829 line:80%
Really nice.

190
00:17:59.913 --> 00:18:01.331 line:80%
-You're so pretty.
-Yeah.

191
00:18:01.414 --> 00:18:02.540 line:80%
Yeah.

192
00:18:04.167 --> 00:18:06.336 line:80%
Hey, wait! Stop!

193
00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:20.433 line:80%
Hey.

194
00:18:24.395 --> 00:18:25.605 line:80%
You're eating well.

195
00:18:27.315 --> 00:18:28.483 line:80%
Here's four.

196
00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:34.364 line:80%
I'll give you nine. Eat it all.

197
00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:38.660 line:80%
Eat it slowly.

198
00:18:40.495 --> 00:18:41.830 line:80%
Drink some water.

199
00:18:48.628 --> 00:18:50.755 line:80%
You'll get fat if you eat like that.

200
00:19:08.690 --> 00:19:10.191 line:80%
CAT SNACKS

201
00:20:21.262 --> 00:20:24.223 line:80%
Ji-hyuk. Why are you always here
during your break?

202
00:20:26.351 --> 00:20:28.269 line:80%
-What is it?
-What is he doing?

203
00:20:28.895 --> 00:20:32.982 line:80%
-Did his senior ask him to make something?
-His service must be tough.

204
00:21:07.475 --> 00:21:09.686 line:80%
Thinking back, I had a few chances.

205
00:21:17.360 --> 00:21:19.737 line:80%
I didn't seize it because I didn't know.

206
00:21:22.782 --> 00:21:25.618 line:80%
Or I couldn't seize it.

207
00:21:27.370 --> 00:21:30.832 line:80%
2011 U&K FOOD
THE MOST INFLUENTIAL FOOD BRAND

208
00:21:30.915 --> 00:21:33.668 line:80%
I would like to introduce our team.

209
00:21:33.751 --> 00:21:34.961 line:80%
Yes...

210
00:21:35.086 --> 00:21:38.089 line:80%
-And if that wasn't it...
-She's a Hankuk University alum.

211
00:21:38.172 --> 00:21:39.590 line:80%
Her name's Kang Ji-won.

212
00:21:39.674 --> 00:21:41.217 line:80%
Say hello.

213
00:21:42.468 --> 00:21:46.055 line:80%
As of today, Mr. Yu Ji-hyuk
will be our general manager.

214
00:21:47.598 --> 00:21:51.227 line:80%
Ji-won graduated from Hankuk University,

215
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:53.896 line:80%
but she slacks in her work. Yeah.

216
00:21:53.980 --> 00:21:56.899 line:80%
I have to pay a lot of attention to her.

217
00:21:56.983 --> 00:22:01.320 line:80%
-What happened to the proposal plan?
-You said it was due tomorrow...

218
00:22:01.988 --> 00:22:03.948 line:80%
See? What did I tell you?

219
00:22:04.032 --> 00:22:05.867 line:80%
Let's keep moving.

220
00:22:05.950 --> 00:22:07.243 line:80%
Yeah, well...

221
00:22:16.210 --> 00:22:17.920 line:80%
It was a chance I shouldn't seize.

222
00:22:35.021 --> 00:22:36.773 line:80%
But it's different this time.

223
00:22:38.941 --> 00:22:42.904 line:80%
APRIL 19, 2013

224
00:23:33.579 --> 00:23:34.705 line:80%
I do feel better.

225
00:23:39.210 --> 00:23:40.211 line:80%
What was that?

226
00:23:43.714 --> 00:23:44.966 line:80%
What?

227
00:23:50.263 --> 00:23:51.389 line:80%
What's with that smile?

228
00:23:53.182 --> 00:23:54.600 line:80%
Follow me.

229
00:24:02.275 --> 00:24:04.777 line:80%
Didn't I tell you? He's interested in you.

230
00:24:05.153 --> 00:24:07.572 line:80%
What are you saying? He has a girlfriend.

231
00:24:08.447 --> 00:24:11.117 line:80%
Is that what he said?
Did he say that himself?

232
00:24:11.284 --> 00:24:12.869 line:80%
You're acting so naive.

233
00:24:12.952 --> 00:24:15.204 line:80%
What does that matter?

234
00:24:15.746 --> 00:24:17.206 line:80%
Let me tell you about men.

235
00:24:17.748 --> 00:24:19.750 line:80%
All men cheat.

236
00:24:19.834 --> 00:24:21.919 line:80%
So he has a girlfriend?

237
00:24:22.003 --> 00:24:25.548 line:80%
He could have a wife
and still like someone else! That's men!

238
00:24:25.631 --> 00:24:27.633 line:80%
Do you know what a guy's ideal type is?

239
00:24:27.884 --> 00:24:30.428 line:80%
An unfamiliar woman.

240
00:24:30.511 --> 00:24:32.263 line:80%
That's men! Okay?

